reviewText: I'm glad I watched this DVD but I think I was looking for more..more in the sense of archeology of the area. It seemed very academic or was it my mood. I would like to have seen more of the utensils, china, living items rather than everything architectural. Don't get me wrong. That was interesting but as I said more archeology would have been nice. I'm going for a visit this summer.
Awesome History of Colonial Williamsburg Virginia..5 Stars !

Amazing what was done here. The pictures really show the progress of the reconstruction and makes any reader soooo thankful that
these men took the time and money to preserve our precious history.

If you want to learn more about the Restoration of the 18th century town Williamsburg, Virginia, this is an excellent resource. See many pictures and videos, coupled with narration to tell the story. If you love Williamsburg, this is a MUST!
